translated: Dieden, Bengt Vincent, manager, Romakloster. Born August 30th, 1911 in Flackarp, Malmöhus County, Sweden. First child of landowner Henrik D. and Ebba Baeckström. Married in 1940 to Märta von Schéele. Children: Eva (born 1940), Marianne (1942), Henrik (1944), Johan (1946). Education: Bachelor's degree from Lund University in 1929, Master's degree in Business Administration in 1932, and Civil Engineering degree in 1935. Worked for Swedish Sugar Factory AB in Trellborg (1935-1936), Ardöv (1936-1942), Köpingebro (1942-1944), and managed Roma Sugar Mill since 1944.
